To unite and promote fellowship among military veterans, their families,
and civilian supporters throughout the student, faculty, and staff population
of the university through social and recreational activities for its members;
• to assist the university administration in identifying the needs of current
and prospective student-veterans;
• to educate the community about military veterans’ experiences and
promote an understanding of issues pertaining to student-veterans or
veterans in the community;
• to perpetuate the memories of achievements of the armed services and its
members;
• to foster true American patriotism and good-citizenship
